wiki.content: "Si Veo a Tu Mamá" (English: "If I See Your Mother") is a song by Puerto Rican rapper Bad Bunny from his third studio album YHLQMDLG. It was released on March 2, 2020, as the fourth single from the album. The song was solely written by Bunny with Subelo NEO and Elikai handling the production and it interpolates "The Girl from Ipanema", written by Antônio Carlos Jobim, Vinícius de Moraes and Norman Gimbel, performed by Stan Getz and João Gilberto. "Si Veo a Tu Mamá" talks about an individual who has not yet moved on from his former partner, no matter how much they admitted they are over them and the person of the song willingly went to the mother of his ex about his whereabouts out of curiosity. On February 28, 2020, Bad Bunny announced his third studio album that was revealed to be YHLQMDLG during his performance and guest appearance on The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, which was released the following day. Following the releasing of its parent album, "Si Veo a Tu Mamá" charted at number 32 on the US Billboard Hot 100 dated March 14, 2020, becoming the highest charting track from YHLQMDLG as well as peaking at number 1 on the US Hot Latin Songs chart upon the issue date of March 14, 2020, becoming the highest charting track. In Spain, "Si Veo a Tu Mamá" reached at number 10. A visualizer video for the song was uploaded to YouTube on February 29, 2020, along with the other visualizer videos of the songs that appeared on YHLQMDLG. A music video for "Si Veo a Tu Mamá" was released on March 2, 2020 on YouTube. Read more on Last.fm.
